<Trigger>
    <UserStory>
        <Name>NCB - LOCALHOST - IIBWebServiceSOAPStub</Name>
        <Description>
            As an insurance agent, I want to retrieve the claim details for a specific policy so that I can process the claim efficiently.
        </Description>
    </UserStory>
    <AcceptanceCriteria>
        <Criteria>
            The SOAP client should be able to retrieve claim details for a specific policy by providing valid inputs.
        </Criteria>
        <Criteria>
            The client should throw an exception if any of the inputs are missing or invalid.
        </Criteria>
        <Criteria>
            The client should handle any errors returned by the external API and provide informative error messages to the user.
        </Criteria>
    </AcceptanceCriteria>
    <DefinitionOfDone>
        <Task>
            The code for the SOAP client should be implemented and tested to ensure it retrieves claim details correctly for valid inputs.
        </Task>
        <Task>
            The client should be tested with different combinations of input parameters to verify that it correctly handles different scenarios and edge cases.
        </Task>
        <Task>
            The client should be properly documented, including usage instructions and any known limitations or issues.
        </Task>
        <Task>
            The client should be integrated into the existing insurance processing system and deployed to production.
        </Task>
    </DefinitionOfDone>
</Trigger>